codex
The ranked hypotheses are:

1. The E2E dashboard fixture omits the canonical `pending_actions.can_start_application` flag, so the real portal intentionally never renders “New Application.”
2. The mocked current-user envelope/session shape fails borrower-role restoration, leaving the app on staff login.
3. The route pattern misses the actual dashboard request, leaving the dashboard in loading/error state.

The first is most likely because the same auth bootstrap works in existing portal specs, and the timeout occurs only at the action button. I’ll verify each prediction against the rendered-action predicate and request paths, then patch only the fixture if confirmed.
